Lk4 is a simple but powerful link forwarding utility.  It consists of a Perl
module (Lk4.pm) and a FastCGI script that together respond to HTTP requests
with the appropriate redirection.  Configuration is done using a simple config
files and may be driven by look-up tables (flat text files or BerkeleyDB files)
as well.

________________________________________________________________________________
INSTALLING

    [edit Makefile as needed]
    make
    sudo make install

Files are installed under /usr/local by default; to change this, specify PREFIX
when installing:

    sudo make install PREFIX=/path/to/install/root

Note that the Perl module and its documentation are installed in
$PREFIX/perl/site_perl while all other files are installed under $PREFIX/lk4.
To change this, you must edit Makefile.

